\begin_layout Proof
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ f_{n}\right\} _{n\in\N}\in\nonnegMeasurableFunctions$
\end_inset

 an increasing sequence of measurable functions.
 Since we are working with the extended non-negative real numbers, we know
 that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f:=\lim_{n\to\infty}f_{n}=\sup_{n\in\N}f_{n}\in\nonnegMeasurableFunctions
\]

\end_inset

by Proposition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "prop:supInfMeasurable"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 Note that by the monotonicity of 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\mu},$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\mu}\left(f_{n}\right)\leq\bar{\mu}\left(f\right)$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $n\in\N$
\end_inset

 and so 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lim_{n\to\infty}\lebInt{\mu}{f_{n}}\leq\lebInt{\mu}f.
\]

\end_inset

To deduce the reverse inequality, let 
\begin_inset Formula $s\leq f$
\end_inset

 be a non-negative measurable simple function, fix some 
\begin_inset Formula $t\in\left(0,1\right)$
\end_inset

